# Project Context

OmniFocus OmniAutomation plug-in collection by Roman Savrulin. All `.omnijs` files are JavaScript executed by the OmniAutomation runtime.

## File Inventory

### Libraries (type: library)

- `st-api-library.omnijs` — shared utility library. Exports `firstURL` / `firstURLFromText` (extract first http(s) URL from text). ID: `com.gmail.romansavrulin.st-api-library`
- `secret-manager-library.omnijs` — centralized credential manager. Stores service registry in `Preferences` (JSON) and secrets in `Credentials` (keychain). Exposes `authenticatedFetch(url, options)` which transparently injects auth headers by URL origin match. ID: `com.gmail.romansavrulin.secret-manager-library`
- `url-resolver-library.omnijs` — extensible URL-to-title resolver chain. Auto-discovers resolver plug-ins via `PlugIn.all` using identifier prefix `com.gmail.romansavrulin.resolver-`. Falls back to HTML title parsing. ID: `com.gmail.romansavrulin.url-resolver-library`
- `resolver-*.omnijs` — individual resolver modules (GitHub, Jira, YouTube, Atushka, etc.). Each is a library exporting `resolverName`, `priority`, `matches(url)`, `resolve(url, fetchFn)`. Auto-discovered by the core resolver library. Note: `PlugIn.Library` has a read-only `name` property, so display names use `resolverName`.

### Actions (type: action)

- `URL-to-TaskName.omnijs` — smart URL handler: if the task name has a URL alongside other text (a caption), extracts the URL to the note and keeps the caption; otherwise resolves the URL to a page title via `url-resolver-library`. Uses `st-api-library` for URL extraction. ID: `com.gmail.romansavrulin.url-to-task-name`
- `copyAsURL.omnijs` — copies tasks as formatted HTML links to clipboard. Uses `st-api-library.firstURLFromText`. ID: `com.gmail.romansavrulin.copy-as-url`
- `ManageSecrets.omnijs` — CRUD UI for secret-manager-library services (list/add/edit/delete credentials). ID: `com.gmail.romansavrulin.manage-secrets`
- `RestTest.omnijs` — StarTrek API test action. Uses `secret-manager-library.authenticatedFetch`. Ctrl+click shows credential status. ID: `com.gmail.romansavrulin.startrek-get`
- `Randomize Review Date.omnijs` — randomizes review dates for selected projects. Standalone, no library deps. ID: `com.gmail.romansavrulin.Randomize-Review-Date`

## Dependency Graph

```
URL-to-TaskName → url-resolver-library → secret-manager-library
                → st-api-library
copyAsURL       → st-api-library
RestTest        → secret-manager-library
ManageSecrets   → secret-manager-library
resolver-*      → (loaded by url-resolver-library, receive fetchFn from secret-manager)
```

## Key Patterns

- All network requests go through `sm.authenticatedFetch()` so auth is injected transparently
- Resolver plug-ins are auto-discovered by identifier prefix `com.gmail.romansavrulin.resolver-`
- Resolver return contract: non-empty string = success, null = fall through, throw = hard error
- `Credentials` and `Preferences` must be instantiated at plug-in load time (IIFE scope)
- Debug logging uses `[resolver]` and `[auth]` prefixes in `console.log`

## Identifier Conventions

- Libraries: `com.gmail.romansavrulin.<name>-library`
- Actions: `com.gmail.romansavrulin.<name>`
- Resolvers: `com.gmail.romansavrulin.resolver-<service>`
